s to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"William Kerdeston was born about 1250 as the son of Roger Kerdeston. He married Margaret Gant or de Gant about 1272, in Ewelme, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died on 1 June 1324, in Loddon, Norfolk, England, at the age of 75, and was buried in Langley, Norfolk, England."},"et":{"Abt 1250–1 June 1324":"umbes 1250–1. juuni 1324","1250–1324":"1250–1324","1253–1284":"1253–1284","1280–1337":"1280–1337","1280–Male":"1280–Surnud","1225–Male":"1225–Surnud","1253":"1253","1284":"1284","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","1315":"1315","1337":"1337","Abt 1250":"umbes 1250","Abt 1272":"umbes 1272","1259":"1259","1225":"1225","1324":"1324","1 June 1324":"1. juuni 1324","Abt 1280":"umbes 1280","1317":"1317","Kerdiston Netherhall Manor, East Ruston, Norfolk, England":"East Ruston, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Loddon, Norfolk, England":"Loddon, Norfolk, England","of Kerdeston, Ewelme, Oxford, England>":"Ewelme, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Langley Abbey, Norfolk, England":"Langley, Norfolk, England","Kerdeston, Ewelme, Oxford, England":"Ewelme, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1250–1 June 1324":"noin 1250–1. kesäkuuta 1324","1250–1324":"1250–1324","1253–1284":"1253–1284","1280–1337":"1280–1337","1280–Male":"1280–Kuollut","1225–Male":"1225–Kuollut","1253":"1253","1284":"1284","1250":"1250","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","1315":"1315","1337":"1337","Abt 1250":"noin 1250","Abt 1272":"noin 1272","1259":"1259","1225":"1225","1324":"1324","1 June 1324":"1. kesäkuuta 1324","Abt 1280":"noin 1280","1317":"1317","Kerdiston Netherhall Manor, East Ruston, Norfolk, England":"East Ruston, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Loddon, Norfolk, England":"Loddon, Norfolk, England","of Kerdes